ZAPPABLES
  wand, staff, rod?

And what they do:

MAGICAL EFFECTS:
" (condiments) ! (potions) ? (scrolls) + (spellbooks?? or not..) *(gems)
= (rings) & (amulets)

Except... rings and amulets might be considered instead to alter your
status; Spellbooks might be considered to add things to your spelllist
(however we implement that)
Don't know what sort of magical effects gems might have.

STATUS VS EFFECTS:
potions, scrolls, gems? and condiments have immediate effects. Rings
and Amulets change your status whilst you wear them.
BUT: The immediate effects of the potions scrolls, etc could be to
alter your status (either permanently, for a short time, etc), and
the status given by the rings and amulets could have you periodically
undergo immediate effects (such as teleporting, etc)!

So, we should have a function that does "effect()", and a function
that does "set_status()". A function "check_status()" could maybe
do the periodical calling of effect() where the status warrants it.

Then, potions, scrolls, gems, condiments (incl foods with them) have
an (*Effect)(void) element, and Rings and Amulets have a Flag element
and a Modifier element.

I think rocks and gems can have many capabilities:
-They can have a status effect whilst carried,
-They can be invoked (eg by rubbing them or whatever),
-They can be lobbed at something or someone!

The throwing effect should be common to many magic items, and should
be an extension of the immediate effect. Maybe those functions given
in each magic item should have an argument "bool thrown" that is
set to 1 when it is thrown, if it's meaningful to do that (not
meaningful with scrolls, for instance), and an argument "eptr subject"
and "eptr target" that get given who activates/throws it and who
its targetted at.

Condiments:
Magical effects of condiments would probably work by imbueing food
with that effect, where the food that has the condiment on gets a
pointer to the condiment-type. When you eat the food, we check that
pointer to see what to do next. Food in general will probably have
some sort of effects anyway, but probably not the same as condiments.

Maybe we could have "rotten" food that could be made OK by certain
condiments (which would alter some flag).

Condiments such as salt and vinegar could pickle foods to stop them
decaying!

WEARABLES:
Armour affects your defensive ability.
Weapons affect your offensive ability.
But perhaps there are some weapons that affect your defensive ability
and armours that affect your offensive ability?
IIRC, Nethack, Adom, and Zangband have these. Prolly others do too.
EG, Gauntlets of Slaying in Zangband have plusses to skill/deadliness.

Perhaps other items should have these characteristics too? Maybe
Not just wearables?
Hmm. Wearables affect you whilst wearing them (as described above),
whereas the other things have some immediate effect. So anything else
that can alter defensive/offensive ability can be described within
those "magical effects" bits described above.
I think.
Hmm, as armour and weapons may have magical effects on status, perhaps
defensive/offensive ability should be a separate one from status
changes, and be on all wearables? But *only* wearables.

BOXES:
Yes, we want boxes and other such containers. Only carrying 15 or so
items is a PITA.

